14 WHEREAS, the State of Oklahoma has a rich history rooted in
15 faith, resilience, and a commitment to values that uplift its
16 people; and
17 WHEREAS, the acknowledgment of spiritual heritage has long been
18 a cornerstone of the cultural identity of Oklahomans, reflecting the
19 beliefs and convictions of many of its citizens; and
20 WHEREAS, the phrase "Christ the King" represents a declaration
21 of faith for millions of Oklahomans and Christians worldwide,
22 symbolizing the sovereignty of Jesus Christ as a source of hope,
23 unity, and moral guidance; and
24
