1 WHEREAS, the Oklahoma State Legislature seeks to affirm the
2 freedom of its citizens to express their deeply held beliefs,
3 including freedom of speech without fear of punishment or
4 retribution, recognizing the importance of religious liberty as
5 enshrined in both the United States Constitution and the Oklahoma
6 Constitution; and
7 WHEREAS, this proclamation serves as an expression of gratitude
8 for the blessings bestowed upon the State of Oklahoma and as a
9 recognition of the enduring influence of Christian faith in the
10 lives of its people.
11 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
12 OF THE 1ST SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE, THE SENATE
13 CONCURRING THEREIN:
14 THAT the Oklahoma State Legislature hereby proclaims "Christ is
15 King", recognizing the spiritual significance of this declaration to
16 many of its citizens and honoring the role of faith in the history
17 and culture of Oklahoma.
18 THAT the Oklahoma State Legislature expresses that this
19 resolution is not intended to establish any religion or infringe
20 upon the rights of any individual, but rather to celebrate the
21 voluntary expression of belief that has shaped communities across
22 the state.
23 THAT copies of this resolution be distributed to the Governor of
24 Oklahoma and the President Pro Tempore of the Oklahoma State Senate,
